.TH "hrtimer_start_range_ns" 9 "hrtimer_start_range_ns" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hrtimer_start_range_ns \- (re)start an hrtimer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" hrtimer_start_range_ns
.BI "(struct hrtimer *timer "  ","
.BI "ktime_t tim "  ","
.BI "u64 delta_ns "  ","
.BI "const enum hrtimer_mode mode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "timer" 12
the timer to be added
.IP "tim" 12
expiry time
.IP "delta_ns" 12
"slack" range for the timer
.IP "mode" 12
timer mode: absolute (HRTIMER_MODE_ABS) or
relative (HRTIMER_MODE_REL), and pinned (HRTIMER_MODE_PINNED);
softirq based mode is considered for debug purpose only!
